	<h2>A ball-rod collision</h2>

	<p>A slender uniform rod of length L and mass M rests along the y-axis on a frictionless and horizontal table contained in the x-y plane. A particle of 
	equal mass M is moving along the x-axis at a speed V<sub>i</sub>. At t=0 the particle strikes the end of the rod and sticks 
	to it. Find the position \(\vec{R}_{cm}(t)\) and the \(\vec{V}_{cm}(t)\)  velocity  of the center of mass as a function of time. 
	Enter Vi for V<sub>i</sub>. (Gravity is into the screen).</p>
<!--
	<p>Type i for \(\vec{i}\), j for \(\vec{j}\), Vi for V<sub>i</sub>.</p>
-->	

	<img src="/static/problems/S13/ESG/images/5-5.png"/>

<p><b>Part a.</b> The position of the center of mass \(\vec{R}_{cm}(t)=X_{cm}(t)\hat{i}+Y_{cm}(t)\hat{j}\)</p>

	<formularesponse samples="Vi,M,L,t@1,1,1,1:10,10,10,10#2" answer="$x">
		<responseparam description="Numerical Tolerance" type="tolerance" default="0.00001" name="tol"/>
		<br/>
		<p> The x-component, \(X_{cm}(t)=\)</p>
		<textline size="40" math="1"/>
	</formularesponse>

    <formularesponse samples="Vi,M,L,t@1,1,1,1:10,10,10,10#2" answer="$y">
		<responseparam description="Numerical Tolerance" type="tolerance" default="0.00001" name="tol"/>
		<br/>
		<p> The y-component, \(Y_{cm}(t)=\)</p>
		<textline size="40" math="1"/>
	</formularesponse>
		
<p><b>Part b.</b> The velocity of the center of mass \(\vec{V}_{cm}(t)=V_{x}(t)\hat{i}+V_{y}(t)\hat{j}\)</p> 		

	<formularesponse samples="Vi,M,L,t@1,1,1,1:10,10,10,10#2" answer="$Vx">
		<responseparam description="Numerical Tolerance" type="tolerance" default="0.00001" name="tol"/>
		<br/>
		<p> The x-component, \(V_{x}(t)=\)</p>
		<textline size="40" math="1"/>
	</formularesponse>
	
<formularesponse samples="Vi,M,L,t@1,1,1,1:10,10,10,10#2" answer="$Vy">
		<responseparam description="Numerical Tolerance" type="tolerance" default="0.00001" name="tol"/>
		<br/>
		<p> The y-component, \(V_{y}(t)=\)</p>
		<textline size="40" math="1"/>
	</formularesponse>
	
